# Phase 8: Finalizing Traveler Movement Context & Forensic Analytics

Integrate the newly added `point_of_entry` field into the broader system's intelligence and reporting layers. This ensures that border command has full situational awareness of movement patterns across all national stations.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> This phase modifies the `seed.js` script to include more diverse historical data. If there is existing manual test data in the database, running the new seed script will TRUNCATE and replace it.

- **Frontend Navigation**: Adding a new "Station Volume" chart to the Dashboard. 
- **Forensic API**: New endpoint for station-based analytics.

## Proposed Changes

### [Backend] Data Logic & Persistence

#### [MODIFY] [seed.js](file:///c:/Users/Mohammed/.gemini/antigravity/ics-backend/seed.js)
- Update crossing seed data to include `point_of_entry`.
- Add more entries with varied stations (Bole, Moyale, Togochale) and timestamps to populate analytics.

#### [MODIFY] [server.js](file:///c:/Users/Mohammed/.gemini/antigravity/ics-backend/server.js)
- Enhance `calculateRiskScore` to include factors for station-based anomalies (e.g., crossing at an unexpected border).
- Update `/api/reports/stats` to include a station-based volume breakdown.
- Ensure crossing history in `/api/risk-profile/:passport` highlights the primary point of entry.

---

### [Frontend] Dashboard & Command Center

#### [MODIFY] [Dashboard.jsx](file:///c:/Users/Mohammed/.gemini/antigravity/ics-frontend/src/pages/Dashboard.jsx)
- Implement a new "Movement by Station" visualization (Bar Chart) to complement the time-series crossing volume.

#### [MODIFY] [History.jsx](file:///c:/Users/Mohammed/.gemini/antigravity/ics-frontend/src/pages/History.jsx)
- Update the "Intelligence" (Analytics) view for the Crossings report to include station distribution.

#### [MODIFY] [TravelerProfile.jsx](file:///c:/Users/Mohammed/.gemini/antigravity/ics-frontend/src/pages/TravelerProfile.jsx)
- Add a "Primary Port" indicator to the traveler's intelligence summary based on their crossing history.

## Open Questions

- Should the Port of Entry be restricted to a predefined list in the backend, or should we continue to allow any string (currently it's a `VARCHAR(100)`)?
- For the Dashboard, should the station volume chart show the "Last 24h" or "All Time" by default?

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Run `node migrate_phase8.js` (ensure it's idenmpotent).
- Run `node seed.js` to populate the new data structure.
- Verify API responses for `/api/reports/stats` using `curl` or manual browser check.

### Manual Verification
- Log in as Administrator.
- Navigate to Dashboard and verify the new "Movement by Station" chart displays data.
- Navigate to Mission Reporting Hub -> Crossings Report -> Intelligence and verify the station distribution chart.
- Search for a specific traveler and verify their "Primary Port" is highlighted in their profile.
